<subSubSection pageId="36" pageNumber="487" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="36.[151,1437,151,645]" box="[199,701,510,537]" pageId="36" pageNumber="487">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,510,536]" pageId="36" pageNumber="487">Distribution.</emphasis>
<collectingCountry box="[359,445,511,537]" name="Mexico" pageId="36" pageNumber="487">Mexico</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion box="[460,566,511,537]" country="Mexico" name="Veracruz de Ignacio de la Llave" pageId="36" pageNumber="487">Veracruz</collectingRegion>
), 
<collectingCountry box="[584,697,511,537]" name="Honduras" pageId="36" pageNumber="487">Honduras</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="36.[151,1437,151,645]" pageId="36" pageNumber="487">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,354,546,572]" pageId="36" pageNumber="487">Comparison.</emphasis>
The new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Gauld et al." authorityName="Gauld" box="[684,924,547,573]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Pimpla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="487" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carlosi">
<emphasis box="[684,789,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="487">P. carlosi</emphasis>
Gauld 
<emphasis box="[869,917,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="487">et al</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicName>
by having tergites 2–7 black with narrow pale posterior band, and short unusually thin ovipositor, but differs from this species by much more extensively yellow marked head, mesosoma and legs (
<figureCitation box="[542,628,619,645]" captionStart="FIGURES 21–23" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1850,1874]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,345,1826]" captionTargetId="figure-92@14.[151,1436,345,1826]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 21–23. Pimpla spp., holotypes, females, habitus, lateral: 21—P. oaxacana sp. nov.; 22—P. tequila sp. nov.; 23—P. xalapana sp. nov." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5726407" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5726407/files/figure.png" pageId="36" pageNumber="487">Figs 23</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[640,715,618,645]" captionStart="FIGURES 54–57" captionStartId="35.[151,264,1445,1469]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,345,1414]" captionTargetId="figure-87@35.[151,1436,345,1421]" captionTargetPageId="35" captionText="FIGURES 54–57. Pimpla xalapana sp. nov., female, paratype: 54—head, front; 55—metasoma, dorsal; 56—mesosoma, lateral; 57—hind leg, lateral." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5726435" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5726435/files/figure.png" pageId="36" pageNumber="487">54–57</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
